            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:text="A problem commonly seen among beginners is when they see a bird, they immediately take the guide to identify it based mainly on the colours of the bird." />
            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:text="Using this approach will lead to frustration due to the large number of birds that have similar colours and shapes." />
            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:text="To get the most accurate identification, it is best to observe the bird before it flies away. Pay attention to details such as size, colour, behaviour, and any other distinctive features. Then, use this information to refer to a bird guide for identification." />

            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:text="As with any skill, it may take time and practice to become proficient at identifying birds. While it is possible that you may make mistakes along the way, even experts make mistakes at times. However, with patience and persistence, you will improve your abilities." />

            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:text="To aid in your efforts, consider following these guidelines." />
            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/shapeandsize"
                style="@style/headingforinfo"
                android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                android:background="@color/ilalalight"
                android:text="Shape and Size" />
            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:text="Size"
                android:textSize="18sp"
                android:textStyle="bold" />
            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:layout_marginTop="0dp"
                android:text="When trying to identify a bird based on its size, it can be helpful to compare it to other birds that you are familiar with." />
            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:text="You might ask yourself if the bird is bigger or smaller than a pigeon. " />
            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:layout_marginBottom="10dp"
                android:text="If the bird is in the company of another known bird, the size difference can be used as a reference." />
            <ImageView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:adjustViewBounds="true"
                android:paddingLeft="20dp"
                android:paddingRight="20dp"
                android:scaleType="fitXY"
                android:src="@drawable/zzz_sizecomparrison" />
            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:text="However, when trying to identify a bird flying high in the sky, be mindful of the fact that there is no reference point for comparison, so size may not be the most reliable characteristic to use." />
            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:text="Shape"
                android:textSize="18sp"
                android:textStyle="bold" />
            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:layout_marginTop="0dp"
                android:layout_marginBottom="10dp"
                android:text="Birds belonging to the same family often have similar shapes, making it easier to group a bird into a specific category or family.
Herons all tend to have a similar shape regardless of their size.
" />
