                android:textStyle="bold" />
            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:layout_marginTop="0dp"
                android:text="Each bill has evolved specifically to help the bird gather and consume food, reflecting their adaptations. This makes the shape and size of a bird's bill an important characteristic for identification, as it can provide a lot of information about the bird's diet and feeding habits." />
            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:text="Piscivore"
                android:textStyle="bold" />
            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:layout_marginTop="0dp"
                android:text="These birds generally have long, slender, pointed beaks for hunting fish, frogs, crustaceans, and other prey in the water. They typically grab their prey between their upper and lower beak but may also use their sharp beak to spear it." />
