            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:layout_marginTop="0dp"
                android:text="Colouration can be a valuable tool for identifying birds, but it can also be a source of confusion. The appearance of a bird's feathers in the field can be affected by the light, angle, and the distance from which it is viewed. " />

            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:text="In addition, a bird's plumage may vary based on its sex, age, and the time of year. Unless the bird has a unique coloration like that of a Crimson-breasted Shrike, it is likely that there are several species with similar plumage." />

            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:text="When looking at Colouration, try to determine the overall colour of the bird otherwise, if there are more than one colour, try to determine where the colours are found on the bird." />

            <TextView
                style="@style/textinfo"
                android:text="Ask yourself, does the bird have a white belly, what is the colour of the back, does it have a distinctive crown on the head, or what colour is the vent?" />


